<font color="#FF0000">MORE THANKS!</font><br>
<tt>Mon Apr  7 22:08:25 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
When you allow yourself to become vulnerable, and express yourself in ways long misplaced, deeply buried, and painful, and with complete honesty, it truly does rekindle a  forgotten faith in human nature when one's words are received with respect, dignity, and fair consideration. Such is my experience on these pages, and my experience with the people who, for better or for worse, provided the stage for this Vietnam Veteran's journey out of a darkness toward the light.<br><br>
I discovered not only a portion of myself, my self esteem, and other people just like myself, but a spark within that I had thought was long extinguished by events so long ago. I began to write, again.<br><br>
My writing here, and now in other places, exposed to the view of the world, is bittersweet. The joy of communicating and being understood is balanced by fear and the pain of the content. That is truly not a bad deal, for the alternative of slow suffocation through exile and passive internalization of conflict would surely have taken the grim reaper's toll. It was only a matter of time.<br><br>
To the POV people who have given of themselves in this exploration, you are to be held in high esteem. Regardless of the outcome, we all won here, and that feels real good.<br><br>
It *is* good to be finally home.<br><br>
Thanks... 
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


